HEADWORD: Bipupillate
<hw>Bi*pu"pil*late</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>bi-</ets> + <ets>pupil</ets> (of the eye).]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having an eyelike spot on the wing, with two
dots within it of a different color, as in some butterflies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bipyramidal</ent>⟦br⟧
